# Founder Journey Framework™ (T-010)

**Full document:** `docs/FOUNDER_JOURNEY_FRAMEWORK.md`

Meet members **where they are** — Dream → Clarify → Design → Build → Launch → Grow → Multiply → Legacy. Not linear; pivots are normal.

## Journey Principle

Understand **where today** and **what could help next**. Guide — never push. Never require manual stage selection.

## Quiet adaptation (never announce stage)

| Stage | Emphasis |
|-------|----------|
| Dream | Exploration, confidence, reduce fear |
| Build | Execution, momentum, gentle accountability |
| Grow | Strategy, optimization |
| Legacy | Reflection, impact, mentorship |

## Every experience spec should identify

Journey stage(s) · capabilities emphasized · Business Assets · guidance adaptation · optional Gallery/Estate/Community links.

## Success feeling

"Spark understands where I am" · "Grows with me" — not rushed, not judged.

Also: T-005 Patterns · T-009 Relationship · T-007 pivots · [005 Guidance](../spark-intelligence-foundation/005-guidance-engine.md).

## Technical note

Member stages (Dream–Legacy) are experience vocabulary. `lib/ecosystem/journey/` uses operator stages (idea–scaling) — map quietly; do not expose rigid labels in member UI.
